macrosystem
------------------------------------------
MacroSystem is a powerful C++ template system designed to separate data
processing from content generation. With MacroSystem you can do recursive macro
replacing, nested if-else and ifnot-else constructs, easy importing and
exporting of macro files. It has been used to create dynamic web content, mail
template systems, and many kinds of preprocessing utilities.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.0-0.212.g6af8fea4bbad
  libgcc1-12.4.0-3
  libmacrosystem-devel-0.51-1bl2
  libmacrosystem0-0.51-1bl2
  libstdc++6-12.4.0-3
  pkg-config-2.3.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-2
  automake-20240607-1
  binutils-2.43.1-1
  cygport-0.36.9-1
  gcc-core-12.4.0-3
  gcc-g++-12.4.0-3
  libtool-2.5.3-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://sourceforge.net/projects/macrosystem/

Canonical download:
  mirror://sourceforge/macrosystem/macrosystem-0.51.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack macrosystem-0.51-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./macrosystem-0.51-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/macrosystem-0.51-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/macrosystem-0.51-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libmacrosystem0-0.51-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libmacrosystem-devel-0.51-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(macrosystem)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/macrosystem.README
  /usr/share/doc/macrosystem/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/macrosystem/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/macrosystem/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/macrosystem/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/macrosystem/README

(libmacrosystem0)
  /usr/bin/cygmacrosystem-0.dll

(libmacrosystem-devel)
  /usr/include/macrosystem.hh
  /usr/lib/libmacrosystem.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/macrosystem.pc

